{
  "texts": [
    "One must acknowledge at the very least the existence of an enhanced privacy risk, as the number of cells gets deeper.",
    "Consider the voter registration files example.",
    "In the US, it is not uncommon to generate predictions from Voter Registration files at far deeper levels of granularity (Nickerson and Rogers 2014).",
    "In effect, VR files work as an individual-level stratification frame.",
    "Predictions can be made-and are often made-at the individual-level."
  ]
}